100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 11, 1925, the League of Nations held discussions aimed at improving international cooperation, with particular focus on disarmament. In the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to stir public sentiment, as various groups rallied for and against the ban on alcohol. Meanwhile, in the world of sports, heavyweight boxing champion Jack Dempsey announced plans for his next title defense, generating excitement among fans nationwide.
